================================
CATEGORY 2: STRUCTURAL PATTERNS
================================
DEFINITION:
Structural patterns explain how to assemble objects and classes into larger 
structures while keeping these structures flexible and efficient. They focus 
on how classes and objects are composed to form larger subsystems.

CORE GOALS:
- Ensure that if one part of a system changes, the entire structure doesn't break.
- Use inheritance or interfaces to allow incompatible objects to work together.
- Organize relationships between entities to simplify the "architecture" of the code.

COFFEE SHOP CONTEXT:
Think of the shop's physical and organizational layout. How does the 
European espresso machine plug into the American wall outlet? (Adapter). 
How does the "Super-Automatic" button hide the complex plumbing and 
grinding inside? (Facade). How do we add whipped cream or sprinkles to 
a base coffee without creating a brand-new menu item for every combo? (Decorator).